Path: godot/classes/class_label3d.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties available for configuring a Label3D node, including text rendering, appearance, and behavior.

- alpha_antialiasing_edge (float): Threshold at which antialiasing will be applied on the alpha channel. Default: 0.0
  Method: set_alpha_antialiasing_edge(value: float)
  Method: get_alpha_antialiasing_edge()
- alpha_antialiasing_mode (AlphaAntiAliasing): The type of alpha antialiasing to apply. Default: 0
  Method: set_alpha_antialiasing(value: AlphaAntiAliasing)
  Method: get_alpha_antialiasing()
- alpha_cut (AlphaCutMode): The alpha cutting mode to use for the sprite. Default: 0
  Method: set_alpha_cut_mode(value: AlphaCutMode)
  Method: get_alpha_cut_mode()
- alpha_hash_scale (float): The hashing scale for Alpha Hash. Recommended values between 0 and 2. Default: 1.0
  Method: set_alpha_hash_scale(value: float)
  Method: get_alpha_hash_scale()
- alpha_scissor_threshold (float): Threshold at which the alpha scissor will discard values. Default: 0.5
  Method: set_alpha_scissor_threshold(value: float)
  Method: get_alpha_scissor_threshold()
- autowrap_mode (AutowrapMode): If set to something other than TextServer.AUTOWRAP_OFF, the text gets wrapped inside the node's bounding rectangle. If you resize the node, it will change its height automatically to show all the text. Default: 0
  Method: set_autowrap_mode(value: AutowrapMode)
  Method: get_autowrap_mode()
- autowrap_trim_flags (bitfield[LineBreakFlag]): Autowrap space trimming flags. See TextServer.BREAK_TRIM_START_EDGE_SPACES and TextServer.BREAK_TRIM_END_EDGE_SPACES for more info. Default: 192
  Method: set_autowrap_trim_flags(value: bitfield[LineBreakFlag])
  Method: get_autowrap_trim_flags()
- billboard (BillboardMode): The billboard mode to use for the label. Default: 0
  Method: set_billboard_mode(value: BillboardMode)
  Method: get_billboard_mode()
- double_sided (bool): If true, text can be seen from the back as well, if false, it is invisible when looking at it from behind. Default: true
  Method: set_draw_flag(flag: DrawFlags, enabled: bool)
  Method: get_draw_flag(flag: DrawFlags) -> bool
- fixed_size (bool): If true, the label is rendered at the same size regardless of distance. The label's size on screen is the same as if the camera was 1.0 units away from the label's origin, regardless of the actual distance from the camera. The Camera3D's field of view (or Camera3D.size when in orthogonal/frustum mode) still affects the size the label is drawn at. Default: false
  Method: set_draw_flag(flag: DrawFlags, enabled: bool)
  Method: get_draw_flag(flag: DrawFlags) -> bool
- font (Font): Font configuration used to display text.
  Method: set_font(value: Font)
  Method: get_font()
- font_size (int): Font size of the Label3D's text. To make the font look more detailed when up close, increase font_size while decreasing pixel_size at the same time. Higher font sizes require more time to render new characters, which can cause stuttering during gameplay. Default: 32
  Method: set_font_size(value: int)
  Method: get_font_size()
- horizontal_alignment (HorizontalAlignment): Controls the text's horizontal alignment. Supports left, center, right, and fill (also known as justify). Default: 1
  Method: set_horizontal_alignment(value: HorizontalAlignment)
  Method: get_horizontal_alignment()
- justification_flags (bitfield[JustificationFlag]): Line fill alignment rules. Default: 163
  Method: set_justification_flags(value: bitfield[JustificationFlag])
  Method: get_justification_flags()
- language (String): Language code used for line-breaking and text shaping algorithms. If left empty, the current locale is used instead. Default: ""
  Method: set_language(value: String)
  Method: get_language()
- line_spacing (float): Additional vertical spacing between lines (in pixels), spacing is added to line descent. This value can be negative. Default: 0.0
  Method: set_line_spacing(value: float)
  Method: get_line_spacing()
- modulate (Color): Text Color of the Label3D. Default: Color(1, 1, 1, 1)
  Method: set_modulate(value: Color)
  Method: get_modulate()
- no_depth_test (bool): If true, depth testing is disabled and the object will be drawn in render order. Default: false
  Method: set_draw_flag(flag: DrawFlags, enabled: bool)
  Method: get_draw_flag(flag: DrawFlags) -> bool
- offset (Vector2): The text drawing offset (in pixels). Default: Vector2(0, 0)
  Method: set_offset(value: Vector2)
  Method: get_offset()
- outline_modulate (Color): The tint of text outline. Default: Color(0, 0, 0, 1)
  Method: set_outline_modulate(value: Color)
  Method: get_outline_modulate()
- outline_render_priority (int): Sets the render priority for the text outline. Higher priority objects will be sorted in front of lower priority objects. Default: -1
  Note: This only applies if alpha_cut is set to ALPHA_CUT_DISABLED (default value).
  Note: This only applies to sorting of transparent objects. This will not impact how transparent objects are sorted relative to opaque objects. This is because opaque objects are not sorted, while transparent objects are sorted from back to front (subject to priority).
  Method: set_outline_render_priority(value: int)
  Method: get_outline_render_priority()
- outline_size (int): Text outline size. Default: 12
  Method: set_outline_size(value: int)
  Method: get_outline_size()
- pixel_size (float): The size of one pixel's width on the label to scale it in 3D. To make the font look more detailed when up close, increase font_size while decreasing pixel_size at the same time. Default: 0.005
  Method: set_pixel_size(value: float)
  Method: get_pixel_size()
- render_priority (int): Sets the render priority for the text. Higher priority objects will be sorted in front of lower priority objects. Default: 0
  Note: This only applies if alpha_cut is set to ALPHA_CUT_DISABLED (default value).
  Note: This only applies to sorting of transparent objects. This will not impact how transparent objects are sorted relative to opaque objects. This is because opaque objects are not sorted, while transparent objects are sorted from back to front (subject to priority).
  Method: set_render_priority(value: int)
  Method: get_render_priority()
- shaded (bool): If true, the Light3D in the Environment has effects on the label. Default: false
  Method: set_draw_flag(flag: DrawFlags, enabled: bool)
  Method: get_draw_flag(flag: DrawFlags) -> bool
- structured_text_bidi_override (StructuredTextParser): Set BiDi algorithm override for the structured text. Default: 0
  Method: set_structured_text_bidi_override(value: StructuredTextParser)
  Method: get_structured_text_bidi_override()
- structured_text_bidi_override_options (Array): Set additional options for BiDi override. Default: []
  Method: set_structured_text_bidi_override_options(value: Array)
  Method: get_structured_text_bidi_override_options()
- text (String): The text to display on screen. Default: ""
  Method: set_text(value: String)
  Method: get_text()
- text_direction (Direction): Base text writing direction. Default: 0
  Method: set_text_direction(value: Direction)
  Method: get_text_direction()
- texture_filter (TextureFilter): Filter flags for the texture. Default: 3
  Method: set_texture_filter(value: TextureFilter)
  Method: get_texture_filter()
- uppercase (bool): If true, all the text displays as UPPERCASE. Default: false
  Method: set_uppercase(value: bool)
  Method: is_uppercase()
- vertical_alignment (VerticalAlignment): Controls the text's vertical alignment. Supports top, center, and bottom. Default: 1
  Method: set_vertical_alignment(value: VerticalAlignment)
  Method: get_vertical_alignment()
- width (float): Text width (in pixels), used for autowrap and fill alignment. Default: 500.0
  Method: set_width(value: float)
  Method: get_width()
